09:57.556 --> 10:01.143
Craig, go have a drink, okay?
And don't fuck up the party.

10:01.143 --> 10:04.688
Okay. O-okay.

10:04.688 --> 10:06.857
♪ Better than before... ♪

10:06.857 --> 10:10.193
- Will you put that away?
- What is this place?

10:10.193 --> 10:12.696
- What are you doing?
- This is my office.

10:12.696 --> 10:14.114
[Bunda]
Audrey, there you are.

10:14.114 --> 10:16.742
These are the men
I was telling you about.

10:16.742 --> 10:20.871
Our wonderful idea men,
Zach and Yaniv, fire and ice.

10:20.871 --> 10:23.415
- Zach. Nice to meet you.
- It's a beautiful space here.

10:23.415 --> 10:24.708
Uh, light-filled.

10:24.708 --> 10:26.543
Audrey is the special sauce

10:26.543 --> 10:28.795
that really holds
this place together.

10:28.795 --> 10:30.464
- Special sauce?
- Well, glue.

10:30.464 --> 10:32.007
[stammers]
Glue.

10:32.007 --> 10:33.091
We have to go.

10:33.091 --> 10:36.219
Oh, you must be Alex,
the saleswoman.

10:36.219 --> 10:38.805
Well, you have
a real winner here.

10:38.805 --> 10:40.557
But you must know that,
don't you?

10:40.557 --> 10:42.559
[chuckles]
We have to run upstairs.

10:42.559 --> 10:45.354
Okay, well, the guys had a
question about implementation.

10:45.354 --> 10:47.814
Yes, the memory effects
of the extract,

10:47.814 --> 10:49.441
they're permanent?

10:49.441 --> 10:50.984
Our research
is still ongoing.

10:50.984 --> 10:52.069
- What is he talking about?
- Calm down.

10:52.069 --> 10:53.195
- What memory effects?
- [giggles]

10:53.195 --> 10:54.780
- The extract...
- So nice to meet you.

10:54.780 --> 10:56.156
- What extract.
- We will be right downstairs.

10:56.156 --> 10:57.366
- Okay.
- So, um...

10:57.366 --> 10:59.785
Well, I-I do need you back
in a few minutes.

10:59.785 --> 11:01.286
- It's important.
[Audrey] Okay.

11:03.872 --> 11:06.958
[Leonard] You mind telling me
what you're doing here?

11:06.958 --> 11:11.004
I got business with those guys,
the assholes.

11:11.004 --> 11:13.548
So I need to go up there.

11:13.548 --> 11:15.300
Little late for business.

11:16.593 --> 11:18.970
I guess so, yeah.

11:18.970 --> 11:20.430
Is that gonna be a problem?

11:24.351 --> 11:27.354
Look, these people,
they did something to me,

11:27.354 --> 11:30.065
and now they're coming
after me.

11:30.065 --> 11:32.776
And so I'm going up there
to talk to them about it.

11:32.776 --> 11:34.986
Is that gonna be a problem
with you?

11:38.657 --> 11:41.785
[flashlight clicks]

11:41.785 --> 11:43.995
You're one of those kids,
aren't you?

11:45.997 --> 11:47.165
What?

11:47.165 --> 11:49.292
From the treatment program?

11:49.292 --> 11:52.295
[dramatic music]

11:52.295 --> 11:55.924
♪ ♪

11:55.924 --> 11:58.844
Come on inside.
We'll talk.

11:58.844 --> 12:05.851
♪ ♪

12:18.196 --> 12:20.240
[Leonard]
You're coming in or not?

12:20.240 --> 12:26.621
♪ ♪

12:32.961 --> 12:35.505
Walter Cruz.

12:35.505 --> 12:37.466
That's you, isn't it?

12:37.466 --> 12:41.511
♪ ♪

12:41.511 --> 12:42.846
Looks like you.

12:42.846 --> 12:45.849
[tense music]

12:45.849 --> 12:52.856
♪ ♪

12:59.571 --> 13:01.573
Who are you?

13:05.702 --> 13:07.370
Who is that?

13:11.374 --> 13:13.293
Walter Cruz.

13:16.713 --> 13:18.173
He did this to me?

13:21.176 --> 13:22.761
He must have.

13:22.761 --> 13:25.222
What was I doing?
Why was I there?

13:25.222 --> 13:28.058
You were talking to him.

13:28.058 --> 13:30.060
About what?

13:30.060 --> 13:32.646
It's your job.

13:32.646 --> 13:35.273
If someone has a problem
with the company, a grievance,

13:35.273 --> 13:36.942
the company hires you.

13:36.942 --> 13:40.487
You convince whoever it is
to back off their claim.

13:40.487 --> 13:43.114
- That's a job?
- You made it a job.

13:44.199 --> 13:46.076
What was his claim?

13:47.911 --> 13:52.541
We were testing the extract
on him,

13:52.541 --> 13:54.668
and there was an accident.

13:56.836 --> 13:59.464
So I was going to get you
out of that?

13:59.464 --> 14:00.882
Yeah.

14:04.553 --> 14:08.181
[dramatic music]

14:08.181 --> 14:10.141
What about my tattoo?

14:10.141 --> 14:12.769
♪ ♪

14:12.769 --> 14:14.187
You don't have one.

14:14.187 --> 14:18.942
I did.
A fake one and a fake ID.

14:18.942 --> 14:20.735
Why did I have all of that

14:20.735 --> 14:23.697
if I was just going to talk
to him?

14:23.697 --> 14:24.948
It's complicated.

14:24.948 --> 14:26.950
Just answer
the fucking question.

14:26.950 --> 14:29.369
♪ ♪

14:29.369 --> 14:31.121
Why?
What difference would it make?

14:31.121 --> 14:33.790
Because I know I did something.

14:33.790 --> 14:37.294
I felt that
the moment I woke up.

14:37.294 --> 14:39.546
I can't say it,

14:39.546 --> 14:41.256
but I can feel it.

14:41.256 --> 14:48.263
♪ ♪

14:50.348 --> 14:53.518
He was a threat.

14:53.518 --> 14:55.312
You were taking control
of the situation

14:55.312 --> 14:57.814
because that's what you do.

14:57.814 --> 14:59.065
We had a choice

14:59.065 --> 15:01.860
between what he wanted
and what we wanted,

15:01.860 --> 15:06.323
between winning and losing,
and we chose us.

15:06.323 --> 15:08.033
"Us"?

15:08.033 --> 15:10.285
Yes.

15:10.285 --> 15:13.997
We take care of each other
because no one else will...

15:13.997 --> 15:16.041
you, me, our family.

15:16.041 --> 15:18.668
Everything else, everyone else,

15:18.668 --> 15:20.420
they're just people.

15:20.420 --> 15:23.423
[ominous music]

15:23.423 --> 15:30.013
♪ ♪

15:31.431 --> 15:34.434
I have to go downstairs
for a minute.

15:35.935 --> 15:37.604
Will you come with me, please?

15:37.604 --> 15:42.150
♪ ♪

15:42.150 --> 15:45.445
And then we can go home.

15:45.445 --> 15:48.948
♪ ♪

15:55.997 --> 15:58.166
So they just erased it all?

16:03.213 --> 16:04.547
[Leonard]
Yeah.

16:07.133 --> 16:08.301
Why?

16:10.011 --> 16:13.431
I guess they thought you'd be
more useful without it.

16:16.726 --> 16:17.936
Can you fix it?

16:19.854 --> 16:21.231
No, no, I can't.

16:21.231 --> 16:23.733
I'm...
I'm sorry.

16:28.488 --> 16:31.116
[folder thuds]

16:34.202 --> 16:37.122
Then finish it.

16:37.122 --> 16:38.790
Finish what?

16:38.790 --> 16:41.084
The job you started.

16:41.084 --> 16:42.502
Take the rest.

16:44.587 --> 16:46.798
I don't, uh...

16:46.798 --> 16:48.925
- I don't understand.
- Yes, you do.

16:50.135 --> 16:52.303
- Can you do it or not?
- That's not the point.

16:52.303 --> 16:53.805
You can do it.
I know you can.

16:53.805 --> 16:56.891
Look, you got a raw deal.
It's not fair what we did...

16:56.891 --> 16:59.310
I don't give a fuck
about fair, okay?

16:59.310 --> 17:01.187
Now, I'm telling you
what I need from you.

17:01.187 --> 17:03.314
- I understand.
- No, you don't.

17:03.314 --> 17:04.357
You can't.

17:08.945 --> 17:11.322
My name is Walter Cruz.

17:11.322 --> 17:12.615
Yes, I know.

17:12.615 --> 17:15.702
I'm from Georgia.
I went to Valdosta High.

17:15.702 --> 17:17.787
All right.

17:17.787 --> 17:20.290
I ran track,
I was in theater tech,

17:20.290 --> 17:23.168
and I had a girlfriend
I didn't like for three years.

17:23.168 --> 17:24.753
Her name was Kat.

17:24.753 --> 17:26.755
And then I had a girlfriend
I really liked senior year.

17:26.755 --> 17:28.548
Her name was Jade.

17:28.548 --> 17:29.883
Jade was a Scorpio.

17:29.883 --> 17:32.844
She had five scorpion tattoos
all over her body.

17:32.844 --> 17:35.680
One was at the bottom
of her foot.

17:35.680 --> 17:38.516
My mother's name is Gloria.
She's a-a Marxist.

17:38.516 --> 17:40.769
I still don't even know
what the fuck that means.

17:42.771 --> 17:44.355
Uh, what are you talking about?

17:44.355 --> 17:46.649
I remember all that.

17:46.649 --> 17:50.987
I remember the enlistment
center and--and my deployment

17:50.987 --> 17:52.989
and seeing the desert
for the first time.

17:52.989 --> 17:55.033
[dramatic music]

17:55.033 --> 17:56.785
But after that, it stops.
It's...

17:56.785 --> 17:59.329
♪ ♪

17:59.329 --> 18:02.791
My service, coming home...

18:02.791 --> 18:05.460
♪ ♪

18:05.460 --> 18:06.961
It's all gone.

18:06.961 --> 18:11.257
♪ ♪

18:11.257 --> 18:14.928
So focus on what you do have.
You can build from there...

18:14.928 --> 18:17.972
No, no, okay?
No.

18:17.972 --> 18:20.099
Look, these memories,
they're....

18:20.099 --> 18:22.393
All they're doing is reminding
me of what's missing.

18:24.062 --> 18:28.274
It's like I got this ache.

18:28.274 --> 18:30.902
It's just...it never stops.
It's fucking rotting in there.

18:30.902 --> 18:32.654
So you want me to poison you?

18:32.654 --> 18:34.906
No, I want you
to finish the job.

18:34.906 --> 18:36.115
Take the rest.

18:36.115 --> 18:37.659
You want to help me?
This is how you help me.

18:37.659 --> 18:40.829
I could take you down
to the fucking studs.

18:40.829 --> 18:44.165
That wouldn't
make a difference.

18:44.165 --> 18:47.043
Now listen to yourself.
What do you want?

18:48.419 --> 18:49.629
You want more.

18:49.629 --> 18:51.589
♪ ♪

18:51.589 --> 18:53.716
That fucking stuff,
you can't manage it.

18:53.716 --> 18:57.303
Once it gets inside,
it grabs on, takes over.

18:58.555 --> 19:01.432
It happened to my company,
my farm.

19:01.432 --> 19:03.560
Fucking happened to me, okay?

19:05.353 --> 19:08.898
Now they're having
a party up there tomorrow

19:08.898 --> 19:11.442
to fucking celebrate.

19:11.442 --> 19:14.445
- Celebrate what?
- I don't know.

19:14.445 --> 19:18.241
More of you.
Something like that.

19:18.241 --> 19:24.038
♪ ♪

19:24.038 --> 19:26.082
You mean they're
doing it again?

19:26.082 --> 19:28.209
And you're just gonna blame it
on some plant?

19:28.209 --> 19:30.295
What do you want me
to say, man?

19:30.295 --> 19:33.006
I...I tried.

19:33.006 --> 19:36.759
You grew it.
It's your company.

19:36.759 --> 19:38.469
You're just hiding out
in some fucking hut?

19:38.469 --> 19:40.263
There's a building
full of them.

19:40.263 --> 19:41.764
There's one of me.

19:41.764 --> 19:43.266
I'm fucking old.

19:43.266 --> 19:45.852
♪ ♪

19:45.852 --> 19:47.729
[scoffs]

19:47.729 --> 19:49.105
You're not old.

19:50.899 --> 19:52.859
You just got a shitty attitude.

19:52.859 --> 19:58.865
♪ ♪

20:00.283 --> 20:03.286
[indistinct shouting]

20:11.961 --> 20:14.964
Audrey, you did it!
Leonard's toast.

20:14.964 --> 20:16.716
We can finally have
some fun around here.

20:16.716 --> 20:18.927
You're not drinking yet?
Let me get you a drink.

20:18.927 --> 20:19.844
No.

20:19.844 --> 20:22.847
[shouting continues]

20:24.515 --> 20:27.644
[cheering]

20:27.644 --> 20:29.771
♪ Wake up, kids ♪

20:29.771 --> 20:32.732
♪ We've got
the dreamers disease... ♪

20:32.732 --> 20:34.150
Thank you.

20:34.150 --> 20:36.527
♪ We got you
down on your knees ♪

20:36.527 --> 20:41.240
♪ So polite, you're busy
still saying please... ♪

20:41.240 --> 20:44.994
Yes, if I can have
your attention for a moment.

20:44.994 --> 20:47.997
I'd like to make
a little toast.

20:47.997 --> 20:50.583
When I was
first deployed,

20:50.583 --> 20:54.420
it was 700 men and me.

20:54.420 --> 20:59.509
I was smiled at and tolerated
and pushed aside.

20:59.509 --> 21:03.054
Twelve years later,
I ran that unit.

21:03.054 --> 21:04.722
♪ ♪

21:04.722 --> 21:06.265
When I first came to Geist,

21:06.265 --> 21:10.979
I met someone who understood
the potential of this company.

21:10.979 --> 21:14.482
That person was smiled at

21:14.482 --> 21:18.277
and tolerated
and pushed aside.

21:18.277 --> 21:20.279
But that ends today.

21:20.279 --> 21:22.281
Audrey Temple,

21:22.281 --> 21:26.619
I am proud to call you
my partner on this project.

21:26.619 --> 21:30.206
You are
my fucking Helen Keller.

21:30.206 --> 21:32.500
- [applause]
[woman] Good job, Audrey.

21:32.500 --> 21:37.088
We are doing this today
because of you.

21:37.088 --> 21:38.798
[voice fades]
We're the meteors,

21:38.798 --> 21:41.801
and those dinosaurs
didn't see us coming.

21:41.801 --> 21:44.804
[foreboding music]

21:44.804 --> 21:51.811
♪ ♪

22:03.906 --> 22:08.536
Here's to new beginnings
and being seen.

22:08.536 --> 22:10.538
- [cheering]
- Bravo.

22:10.538 --> 22:13.541
[cheers and applause]

22:13.541 --> 22:16.669
[suspenseful music]

22:16.669 --> 22:23.676
♪ ♪

22:29.182 --> 22:31.517
[groans softly]

22:31.517 --> 22:33.519
[grunts softly]

22:33.519 --> 22:40.526
♪ ♪

22:46.991 --> 22:48.993
[groans softly]

22:48.993 --> 22:55.666
♪ ♪

23:06.761 --> 23:09.472
This...this is what we wanted.

23:09.472 --> 23:13.684
♪ ♪

23:13.684 --> 23:15.311
[woman]
Go, Audrey.

23:15.311 --> 23:16.896
[man]
Bottoms up, Audrey!

23:16.896 --> 23:19.899
[scattered cheers]

23:19.899 --> 23:24.695
♪ ♪

23:24.695 --> 23:26.489
Mm.

23:26.489 --> 23:33.079
♪ ♪

23:33.079 --> 23:35.289
[Yaniv]
Whoa, whoa, Zach. Zach.

23:35.289 --> 23:38.543
[groans]

23:38.543 --> 23:41.337
♪ ♪

23:41.337 --> 23:43.339
[crowd gasps]

23:43.339 --> 23:44.173
Oh.

23:44.173 --> 23:45.925
[concerned chatter]

23:45.925 --> 23:47.510
[Audrey]
Oh.

23:47.510 --> 23:49.637
♪ ♪

23:49.637 --> 23:51.389
What's going on?

23:51.389 --> 23:58.396
♪ ♪

24:21.711 --> 24:23.171
Oh, no.

24:23.171 --> 24:26.799
♪ ♪

24:29.760 --> 24:36.767
♪ ♪

25:32.823 --> 25:35.451
[whimpers]

25:35.451 --> 25:37.453
[cup clinks]

25:37.453 --> 25:39.455
[whimpers]

25:51.425 --> 25:53.427
Is it gonna hurt?

25:55.388 --> 25:57.390
[Alex]
I don't remember.

26:06.065 --> 26:07.817
I'm gonna go...

26:13.072 --> 26:14.865
...sit down.

26:14.865 --> 26:16.867
[item clinks]

26:18.077 --> 26:20.079
[shudders]

26:34.093 --> 26:36.512
[shudders]

26:39.682 --> 26:42.518
[inhales shakily]

26:42.518 --> 26:44.895
[gasps]

26:50.943 --> 26:55.072
[laughing] We...we should've
just gone back to bed.

26:57.325 --> 26:58.701
What?

27:01.579 --> 27:04.415
You were right.
Olive...

27:06.709 --> 27:08.586
...that's a pretty name.

27:10.129 --> 27:13.424
[breathes deeply]

27:13.424 --> 27:14.550
Olive.

27:17.261 --> 27:20.264
[solemn music]

27:20.264 --> 27:27.271
♪ ♪

27:44.372 --> 27:47.375
[footsteps approaching]

27:47.375 --> 27:52.588
♪ ♪

27:52.588 --> 27:54.173
[Bunda]
There you are.

27:54.173 --> 27:57.760
♪ ♪

27:57.760 --> 27:59.470
This stuff really works, huh?

28:05.393 --> 28:07.520
How much time do I have?

28:08.604 --> 28:10.022
I don't know.

28:10.022 --> 28:13.067
Depends how much you drank,
I guess.

28:20.866 --> 28:22.618
You know, my, um...

28:24.161 --> 28:27.248
...daughter's getting married
next week.

28:27.248 --> 28:29.917
I'm--I'm supposed
to give her away.

28:42.012 --> 28:44.432
So, um...

28:44.432 --> 28:47.268
What are you gonna just do
with all this--just rip it out?

28:49.228 --> 28:51.439
Yep.
[groans]

28:58.654 --> 29:00.239
What a waste.

29:02.450 --> 29:04.243
I was gonna do something here.

29:04.243 --> 29:07.455
I was gonna do something big!

29:07.455 --> 29:10.666
I was gonna take
a fucking moonshot!

29:10.666 --> 29:12.042
I know that's
what you thought.

29:12.042 --> 29:13.419
And what did you think?

29:13.419 --> 29:15.379
What was your big idea?

29:15.379 --> 29:17.465
I fucked things up
pretty good.

29:19.842 --> 29:22.595
This was the best
I could come up with.

29:24.263 --> 29:26.265
[chuckles]

29:27.850 --> 29:29.810
You know what you are?
You're stubborn.

29:31.061 --> 29:34.690
You just only see things
your way.

29:34.690 --> 29:36.484
Well...

29:36.484 --> 29:39.862
I don't think there's
more than one way to see this.

29:39.862 --> 29:42.865
Of course there is.
There's a million ways.

29:42.865 --> 29:46.076
You put things in context.
You take them out of context.

29:46.076 --> 29:48.871
That's how new ideas happen.

29:48.871 --> 29:51.123
It takes nerve.

29:52.500 --> 29:55.085
Yeah, well...

29:55.085 --> 29:57.713
those are just
fucking song lyrics.

29:57.713 --> 30:01.884
Sound good.
They don't mean anything.

30:01.884 --> 30:05.721
[dog panting]

30:05.721 --> 30:08.724
See?
You're just stubborn.

30:08.724 --> 30:10.893
[chuckles]

30:10.893 --> 30:13.103
I used to be like that.

30:20.319 --> 30:23.239
You're gonna get sunburned
laying out here.

30:24.323 --> 30:25.533
[gasps]

30:25.533 --> 30:27.910
Give me your fucking hat.

30:27.910 --> 30:29.912
[chuckles]

30:37.753 --> 30:40.756
[gasps, exhales sharply]

30:41.924 --> 30:44.218
My hero.

30:44.218 --> 30:47.221
[dramatic music]

30:47.221 --> 30:54.228
♪ ♪

31:46.822 --> 31:48.824
[scoffs]

31:48.824 --> 31:51.118
You don't even remember me,
do you?

31:52.828 --> 31:54.622
No.

31:54.622 --> 31:56.206
I don't.

31:59.627 --> 32:00.836
Who's that?

32:05.424 --> 32:07.551
I don't know really.

32:10.220 --> 32:12.222
[sighs]

32:15.643 --> 32:17.895
You should go now.

32:19.438 --> 32:21.023
I will.

32:23.442 --> 32:26.445
I just know what it's like
to wake up like that...

32:28.447 --> 32:30.032
...alone.

32:49.218 --> 32:50.678
♪ And now ♪

32:50.678 --> 32:53.681
♪ The end is near ♪

32:53.681 --> 32:58.268
♪ And so I got to face
the final curtain ♪

32:58.268 --> 32:59.895
♪ Curtain ♪

32:59.895 --> 33:02.064
♪ Friends ♪

33:02.064 --> 33:04.900
♪ I'll say it clear ♪

33:04.900 --> 33:07.903
♪ And state my case ♪

33:07.903 --> 33:11.073
♪ Of which I'm certain ♪

33:11.073 --> 33:13.492
♪ I've lived ♪

33:13.492 --> 33:16.286
♪ A life that's full ♪

33:16.286 --> 33:19.498
♪ I've traveled each ♪

33:19.498 --> 33:22.501
♪ And every highway ♪

33:22.501 --> 33:24.920
♪ And more ♪

33:24.920 --> 33:27.715
♪ Much more than this ♪

33:27.715 --> 33:30.300
♪ I did it my way ♪

33:30.300 --> 33:33.512
♪ ♪

33:33.512 --> 33:35.931
♪ Regrets ♪

33:35.931 --> 33:40.310
♪ Regrets, I've had a few ♪

33:40.310 --> 33:42.730
♪ But then again ♪

33:42.730 --> 33:45.733
♪ Too few to mention ♪

33:45.733 --> 33:47.943
♪ I did ♪

33:47.943 --> 33:50.738
♪ What I had to do ♪

33:50.738 --> 33:53.323
♪ And saw it through ♪

33:53.323 --> 33:55.743
♪ Without exemption ♪

33:55.743 --> 33:57.745
[keys jingle,
engine turning over]

33:57.745 --> 34:01.832
♪ I planned
each charted course ♪

34:01.832 --> 34:04.960
♪ Each careful footstep ♪

34:04.960 --> 34:08.797
♪ Along the byway, yeah ♪

34:08.797 --> 34:13.552
♪ More, much more than this ♪

34:13.552 --> 34:16.930
♪ I did it my way ♪

34:16.930 --> 34:18.974
♪ ♪

34:18.974 --> 34:21.977
♪ Yes, there were times ♪

34:21.977 --> 34:24.772
♪ I'm sure you knew ♪

34:24.772 --> 34:27.775
♪ When I bit off ♪

34:27.775 --> 34:30.569
♪ Much more
than I could chew ♪

34:30.569 --> 34:33.572
♪ But through it all ♪

34:33.572 --> 34:36.575
♪ When there was doubt ♪

34:36.575 --> 34:39.161
♪ I ate it up ♪

34:39.161 --> 34:41.789
♪ And spat it out ♪

34:41.789 --> 34:44.792
♪ I faced it all ♪

34:44.792 --> 34:47.586
♪ And I stood tall ♪

34:47.586 --> 34:50.589
♪ And did it my way ♪

34:50.589 --> 34:54.384
♪ ♪

34:54.384 --> 34:56.386
♪ Ooh ♪

34:56.386 --> 34:59.389
♪ I've laughed and cried ♪

34:59.389 --> 35:02.392
♪ I've had my fill ♪

35:02.392 --> 35:05.604
♪ My share of losing ♪

35:05.604 --> 35:07.397
♪ And now ♪

35:07.397 --> 35:11.819
♪ As tears subside ♪

35:11.819 --> 35:14.029
♪ I find it all

35:14.029 --> 35:16.824
♪ So amusing ♪

35:16.824 --> 35:19.034
♪ To think ♪

35:19.034 --> 35:21.829
♪ I did all that ♪

35:21.829 --> 35:24.832
♪ And may I say ♪

35:24.832 --> 35:27.626
♪ Not in a sly way ♪

35:27.626 --> 35:30.420
♪ Oh, no, no, no ♪

35:30.420 --> 35:33.215
♪ No, not me ♪

35:33.215 --> 35:36.635
♪ I did it my way ♪

35:36.635 --> 35:39.054
♪ ♪

35:39.054 --> 35:42.641
♪ Oh, what is a man? ♪

35:42.641 --> 35:44.852
♪ What has he got? ♪

35:44.852 --> 35:47.855
♪ If not himself ♪

35:47.855 --> 35:50.649
♪ Then he has naught ♪

35:50.649 --> 35:53.652
♪ To say the things ♪

35:53.652 --> 35:56.655
♪ He truly feels ♪

35:56.655 --> 35:59.449
♪ Not the words ♪

35:59.449 --> 36:02.244
♪ Of one who kneels ♪

36:02.244 --> 36:04.872
♪ The record shows ♪

36:04.872 --> 36:07.666
♪ I took the blows ♪

36:07.666 --> 36:13.881
♪ And did it my way ♪

36:13.881 --> 36:20.888
♪ ♪

37:08.685 --> 37:10.646
[computer beeps,
keys clacking]
